,'2024-08-05 19:20:55','2024-08-05 19:20:55','',91,'https://tech24.wpenginepowered.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/12.jpeg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(127,15,'2024-08-05 19:20:56','2024-08-05 19:20:56','','16','','inherit','open','closed','','16','','','2024-08-05 19:20:56','2024-08-05 19:20:56','',91,'https://tech24.wpenginepowered.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/16.jpeg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(128,15,'2024-08-05 19:20:57','2024-08-05 19:20:57','','17','','inherit','open','closed','','17','','','2024-08-05 19:20:57','2024-08-05 19:20:57','',91,'https://tech24.wpenginepowered.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/17.jpeg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(129,15,'2024-08-05 19:20:58','2024-08-05 19:20:58','','18','','inherit','open','closed','','18','','','2024-08-05 19:20:58','2024-08-05 19:20:58','',91,'https://tech24.wpenginepowered.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/18.jpeg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(130,15,'2024-08-05 19:20:59','2024-08-05 19:20:59','','22','','inherit','open','closed','','22','','','2024-08-05 19:20:59','2024-08-05 19:20:59','',91,'https://tech24.wpenginepowered.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/22.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(131,15,'2024-08-05 19:21:00','2024-08-05 19:21:00','','23','','inherit','open','closed','','23','','','2024-08-05 19:21:00','2024-08-05 19:21:00','',91,'https://tech24.wpenginepowered.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/23.jpeg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(132,15,'2024-08-05 19:21:01','2024-08-05 19:21:01','','31','','inherit','open','closed','','31','','','2024-08-05 19:21:01','2024-08-05 19:21:01','',91,'https://tech24.wpenginepowered.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/31.jpeg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(133,15,'2024-08-05 19:21:02','2024-08-05 19:21:02','','33','','inherit','open','closed','','33','','','2024-08-05 19:21:02','2024-08-05 19:21:02','',91,'https://tech24.wpenginepowered.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/33.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(134,15,'2024-08-05 19:21:04','2024-08-05 19:21:04','','big-data-7186530_1920','','inherit','open','closed','','big-data-7186530_1920','','','2024-08-05 19:21:04','2024-08-05 19:21:04','',91,'https://tech24.wpenginepowered.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/big-data-7186530_1920.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(135,15,'2024-08-05 19:21:06','2024-08-05 19:21:06','','big-data-7644538_1920','','inherit','open','closed','','big-data-7644538_1920','','','2024-08-05 19:21:06','2024-08-05 19:21:06','',91,'https://tech24.wpenginepowered.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/big-data-7644538_1920.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(136,20,'2024-08-05 20:07:38','2024-08-05 20:07:38','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In our contemporary world of constantly expanding data, the issues of data gravity and data mobility are closely intertwined challenges when it comes to handling extensive datasets. Let\'s delve deeper to explore how object storage and COSI are effectively addressing and mitigating these challenges.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Data Gravity</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Data gravity is the phenomenon where large datasets attract applications, services, and additional data. The larger the dataset, the greater its gravitational pull. This is because applications need to be located close to the data to achieve good performance and low latency. As more data and services cluster around large datasets, moving the data becomes difficult and expensive - the data becomes \"heavy\".</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Data Mobility</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Data mobility refers to the ability to efficiently move data between locations, systems, and applications. Good data mobility means being able to access, integrate, migrate, and analyze data across multiple environments with minimal latency or expense. Data gravity makes achieving data mobility more challenging. The larger the dataset, the more difficult and costly it becomes to move.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Object Storage &amp; Data Gravity</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Object storage is a scalable, cost-effective cloud storage solution optimized for storing and managing massive amounts of unstructured data. Object storage helps mitigate data gravity in several ways:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>It allows unlimited scalability, so storage can expand as data grows.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Data can be distributed globally, bringing it closer to applications.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Data accessibility is improved through standard HTTP-based APIs.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Movement of objects between locations is fast and inexpensive. By distributing data globally while maintaining accessibility, object storage makes it easier to overcome data gravity.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Exploring Object Storage in Conjunction with the Ascendance of COSI','In our contemporary world of constantly expanding data, the issues of data gravity and data mobility are closely intertwined challenges when it comes to handling extensive datasets.','publish','open','open','','exploring-object-storage-in-conjunction-with-the-ascendance-of-cosi','','','2024-08-07 20:06:34','2024-08-07 20:06:34','',0,'https://tech24.wpenginepowered.com/?p=136',0,'post','',1),(137,15,'2024-08-05 20:04:00','2024-08-05 20:04:00','','image','','inherit','open','closed','','image','','','2024-08-05 20:04:00','2024-08-05 20:04:00','',136,'https://tech24.wpenginepowered.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/image.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(138,1,'2024-08-05 20:11:36','2024-08-05 20:11:36','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The integration of container technologies has profoundly disrupted the established culture and software development methodologies within the organization. With the advent of containers, traditional approaches to development, patching, and system upgrades may no longer be directly applicable, necessitating a willingness among employees to embrace a new model. To ensure a successful transition, it is crucial for the staff to be open to adapting their practices and methodologies.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In this guide, we will cover recommended practices for securely building and operating applications within containers, offering essential insights for employees to follow. It is of utmost importance for the organization to reevaluate existing procedures to fully capitalize on the benefits that containers can bring.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The primary objective of this document is to shed light on the security concerns associated with container technologies and provide practical recommendations for effectively addressing these concerns throughout the planning, implementation, and maintenance stages of container usage. By heeding these guidelines, the organization can navigate the challenges and intricacies of container security, fostering a safer and more efficient containerized environment.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Overall, embracing containerization and its accompanying best practices will enable the organization to propel its software development processes to new heights while safeguarding against potential security vulnerabilities.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Playbook for Adopting Container Security Solutions','The integration of container technologies has profoundly disrupted the established culture and software development methodologies within the organization.','publish','open','open','','playbook-for-adopting-container-security-solutions','','','2024-08-07 20:03:00','2024-08-07 20:03:00','',0,'https://tech24.wpenginepowered.com/?p=138',0,'post','',0),(139,17,'2024-08-05 20:21:20','2024-08-05 20:21:20','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Goal of Edge Computing</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Contrary to traditional notions, edge computing encompasses more than just reducing latency and improving user experience by bringing computational power and data storage closer to the data source or end-users. At its core, edge computing revolves around the concepts of data mastery and data commercialization. Its ultimate aim is to empower organizations with real- time data control, enabling informed decision-making that enhances key performance indicators (KPIs) and optimizes user experiences while remaining cost-effective.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Edge computing recognizes the significance of gaining comprehensive understanding of data assets, effectively managing them, and utilizing them strategically within an organization. This mastery of data allows businesses to unlock valuable insights, make data-driven decisions, and drive operational efficiency. Simultaneously, edge computing acknowledges the commercial potential of data. By transforming data into marketable products, services, or insights, organizations can create new revenue streams and capitalize on their data assets.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Data commercialization is the process of utilizing a company\'s data to drive business value beyond data monetization. Unlike data monetization which focuses on selling data as a standalone product, data commercialization aims to extract tangible value from data to improve business operations, uncover new opportunities, and create competitive advantages.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Data mastery refers to the comprehensive understanding and management of data within an organization to derive maximum value. It goes beyond data collection and involves processes to gain deep insight into the meaning, accuracy, and potential use cases of data. It enables optimizing data quality, implementing governance practices, and leveraging technologies like machine learning to uncover patterns and trends. The end goal is to establish authoritative knowledge of the organization\'s data landscape and ability to harness data effectively for strategic goals. It empowers data-driven decision making at all levels for increased operational efficiency, risk mitigation, and innovation.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In essence, edge computing surpasses its initial goals and delves into the realms of data mastery and commercialization. It seeks to empower organizations with control over their real- time data, leading to enhanced decision-making, improved KPIs, and optimized user experiences. All of this is accomplished while maintaining a focus on cost-effectiveness and staying at the forefront of technological advancements.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Essentials</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>To unlock the true potential of edge computing in the future, there are essential requirements that must be met.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Consistent &amp; Predictable Low Latency: Consistent and predictable low latency is of utmost importance in edge computing, unlocking its transformative potential. The proliferation of real- time applications necessitates low latency, from autonomous vehicles to industrial automation and augmented/virtual reality. Delays in data processing can lead to critical consequences like safety hazards, production inefficiencies, or degraded user experiences. Consistency and predictability are equally crucial. Reliable response times are essential for uninterrupted user experiences, as inconsistent latency can result in jittery video streams, dropped connections, or data inaccuracies, eroding trust. In conclusion, consistent and predictable low latency in edge computing is indispensable for real-time applications, managing IoT device data, and supporting industries requiring split-second decisions. As edge computing continues to reshape industries, optimizing latency is pivotal for a seamless, efficient, and reliable digital ecosystem.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Resilience To Network Disconnection &amp; Optimized Bandwidth: maintaining resilience to network disconnection is crucial for uninterrupted device functionality in environments with unreliable connectivity. Local data processing and storage enable autonomous operation, reducing reliance on continuous cloud connectivity. Optimizing bandwidth utilization is equally vital, given the growing data volume from IoT devices and real-time applications. Edge computing filters and analyzes data at the edge, minimizing raw data transmission to the cloud and conserving valuable bandwidth. This combined approach ensures continuous operation,</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>enhances data security, and delivers a responsive ecosystem that meets modern application demands. As edge computing evolves, its ability to adapt to network challenges and optimize resource usage solidifies its position as a cornerstone technology across industries.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Zero Trust Security: Zero trust security is crucial in edge computing due to its distributed and dynamic nature. Traditional security models are insufficient for the expanded attack surface in edge environments. Zero trust assumes no inherent trust in any device or entity, requiring continuous identity verification and adherence to security policies. This approach ensures data protection, limits unauthorized access, and adapts to changing conditions. It also aids compliance with data privacy regulations by verifying access rights and encrypting data at the source. Zero trust security is essential for organizations embracing edge computing\'s transformative potential, providing data protection, secure access control, and regulatory compliance in this evolving landscape.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Any-Scale Scalability: Any-scale scalability is a crucial aspect of edge computing that addresses the dynamic and diverse nature of edge environments. In edge computing, where devices come in various sizes and possess different capabilities, any-scale scalability ensures optimal performance and efficient resource utilization. It enables the seamless integration of new devices while supporting real-time analytics and autonomous systems.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>By providing the ability to add or remove devices without disruptions, any-scale scalability allows edge systems to adapt to changing requirements and workloads. It optimizes the allocation of resources, such as processing power and storage, ensuring that tasks are efficiently distributed and executed. This scalability plays a vital role in enhancing the overall performance and responsiveness of edge applications.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>One of the high benefits of any-scale scalability is its ability to future-proof edge infrastructure. As emerging technologies continue to evolve, organizations can easily incorporate these advancements into their edge computing systems without major changes to the underlying infrastructure. This flexibility enables businesses to stay at the forefront of innovation in edge computing and take advantage of new opportunities as they arise.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Furthermore, any-scale scalability contributes to improved operational efficiency and cost- effectiveness. With the ability to scale resources based on demand, organizations can avoid overprovisioning and unnecessary expenses. They can dynamically adjust resources to match the workload, ensuring optimal resource utilization and reducing operational costs.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In conclusion, any-scale scalability in edge provides the flexibility and adaptability required to meet the dynamic demands of edge environments. It enables seamless device integration, supports real-time analytics, optimizes resource allocation, future-proofs infrastructure, and improves operational efficiency, making it a highly beneficial capability in the world of edge computing.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Embracing the Era of Optimized Solutions The Transformative Potential of Edge Computing','','publish','open','open','','embracing-the-era-of-optimized-solutions-the-transformative-potential-of-edge-computing','','','2024-08-05 20:21:20','2024-08-05 20:21:20','',0,'https://tech24.wpenginepowered.com/?p=139',0,'post','',0),(140,22,'2024-08-05 20:27:40','2024-08-05 20:27:40','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>当前谁在用边缘数据中心，用来做什么：目前边缘数据中心的常见应用对数据的使用模式主要有三大类：数据服务（例如电信），数据采入类（例如 IoT 和 ADAS），实时数据处理（例如高端医疗和制造）。按照行业划分，当前在边缘部署中占比较高的行业有：企业, IT，汽车，电信，医疗，零售，制造业，智慧城市和智能电网等基础设施类。在边缘生态中有较大份额是基于微型终端如手机和 IoT 设备，这些对于 IT 设备商不构成直接机会，不在本文讨论范围。但是他们带来的数据会增加边缘设备需求，设备商的机会点集中在下图红框的区域，包含 ROBO，区域中心，接入中心等等场景。</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>边缘数据中心的增长点：未来几年边缘数据应用的趋势主要体现在数据量的高速增长和数据处理的复杂度不断提升。过去两年的疫情给医疗行业带来了巨大增长，边缘数据中心在医疗行业的高速增长不会随着疫情停止，值得持续关注。边缘应用高速增长的板块还有自动驾驶，制造业，企业 IT 服务，智慧城市。此外 Web 3. 0 和元宇宙类应用也值得关注。</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>相比前面的一些相对成熟板块，这两类应用有更高复杂性，对边缘会带来新挑战和机遇，尤其在生态和计算侧。什么样的架构最能满足我们预测的趋势：在边缘数据中心里，运算，存储，网络的三元核心依然成立，并且依然是以计算为核心。已知的重点需求依然有效：统一高效的管理平台，存算合一的模块化部署。在此基础上，由于高成长领域例如 AI/ML 类应用的快速演变，软件应用的生命周期越来越快，对基础架构提出更多挑战。整合云原生容器化平台，验证支持成熟及新锐软件生态将大大增强产品竞争力。硬件方面应增加 GPU/DPU 选项避免被某些机会点屏蔽。传统 HCI 的架构能够降低运维复杂度，减少硬件维度，从而帮助客户整体降低 TCO，是个很好的基座。在软件生态方面必须加强，形成软硬一体的方案。</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>怎样基于现有产品构建更有竞争力的解决方案：以现有 HCI 方案为基础，在软件，硬件，商务三方面加强，提供类云的用户体验和更高的性价比。软件上整合云原生平台，内嵌集成应用模板支持一键部署各类成熟生态体系和开源及商用软件。对于最流行的应用，推出App 专用超融合一体机，例如 Spark 大数据一体机。硬件上提供 GPU/DPU 选项。商务模式方面可以学习 HPE®的 GreenLake 风格的 PayU 模式进一步帮助客户降低 TCO 提高竞争力。制定商务模式很简单，但是能形成差异竞争力的核心技术是用量监测分析工具。</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','A Look into The Future of Edge Data Center','按照行业划分，当前在边缘部署中占比较高的行业有：企业, IT，汽车，电信，医疗，零售，制造业，智慧城市和智能电网等基础设施类。','publish','open','open','','a-look-into-the-future-of-edge-data-center','','','2024-08-28 09:07:20','2024-08-28 09:07:20','',0,'https://tech24.wpenginepowered.com/?p=140',0,'post','',0),(143,18,'2024-08-05 21:02:59','2024-08-05 21:02:59','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p >Primary storage market will continue to grow at a favorable rate in the following years, although there are continuous competitions from server storage as well as public cloud. Slower growth rate (even negative growth rate) may occur in certain categories in primary storage products. It reflects adoptions of new data center strategies and new workload introductions such as AI/Machine Learning, big data and other workloads powered by 5G and other emerging technologies.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>To continuously generate growth, fend off fierce competition from public clouds and server storage and provide more values to customers, primary storage vendors shall focus on several initiatives. Of all the initiatives, one of the key initiatives potentially could be data/application platform integration.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Primary storage market is becoming a red ocean market with increasingly competitions from cloud and among existing vendors. Profits and growth are slowing down. Storage vendors need to expand market space with new value creation. In today and future market, data and application has far more reaching impacts to customer’s business than underlying infrastructure. Application and data platform has controlled data access point resulting in decoupling of infrastructure underlying and applications that use them. Building an integrated application platform by leveraging hardware and underlying infrastructure capabilities could be one of the key competences for primary storage products. </strong>Application platform shall leverage hardware and enterprise capabilities provided by primary storage to offer differentiation among other vendors with full stack optimization.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>With popularity of data mesh methodology, more and more enterprises have decentralized their data, pushing data storage, models, and management into different business units. [1] Whoever controls data entry point will control entire customer data set and therefore, treat underlying infrastructure just as resources from edge, data center and cloud. How does primary storage vendor become major contributor to this effort instead of bystander? It will be the key for the next few years to define the role primary storage is going to play in the data center.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Vendors may often tout their hardware prowess to differentiate themselves from their competitors. Software or platform capabilities, so called “Soft Power”, that could also distance vendor from their competitors. A start-up company may rely on “back technology” to differentiate itself from competitors and incumbents. Growing software capabilities and broader ecosystem supports to meet customer requirements with hardware differentiation as core competence can increase customer stickiness and expand business. They are the driving forces for business grow. It is especially true for sectors that are much mature, for example storage industry.</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>We expect green initiative and carbon emission conscious data center solution will be more important going forward. Countries are implementing more and more related regulations that have bigger impact on enterprises. Carbon emission</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>regulation conforming may become a barrier for enterprises to enter certain IT markets in the future.</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Some primary storage vendors, NetApp® as leading example, have started to transition themselves into public cloud storage companies. It is a bold move. To hedge the risk, we are expecting those vendors will continue to invest their bread and butter – on prem primary storage market.</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Primary Storage Insights','Primary storage market will continue to grow at a favorable rate in the following years, although there are continuous competitions from server storage as well as public cloud. ','publish','open','open','','primary-storage-insights','','','2024-11-19 18:38:14','2024-11-19 18:38:14','',0,'https://tech24.wpenginepowered.com/?p=143',0,'post','',0),(144,18,'2024-08-05 21:09:10','2024-08-05 21:09:10','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>Overview</strong></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>According to IDC, enterprises data is expected to grow to 93 Zettabytes by 2025. About 80% of that data is secondary data in the form of files, objects, and backups. Primary storage typically only comprises 20% of overall capacity. The remaining 80% consists of secondary storage that covers all your secondary use cases, including backup, archiving, file and object storage, dev/test, analytics, private and public cloud.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>As the primary storage market leaders stablized from a spending perspective, the secondary storage market (refers to storage systems for data protection, backup and so on) has seen a big total addressable market (TAM) expansion, with companies like Cohesity® and Rubrik® expanding the notion of data protection from backup into data management, analytics and security.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Secondary storage infrastructure is fragmented across a patchwork of point appliances, including deduplication appliances, backup servers, cloud gateways, NAS, and data</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>lakes. This approach is complex: each needs to be provisioned, configured, managed and updated through its own proprietary UI and processes. Data must be copied and stored across the silos, with enterprises keeping an average of 10 to 15 redundant copies of data across silos. Enterprises need a simpler, more efficient way to manage their ever- increasing volumes of data.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>Cloud Adoption</strong></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>The number of organizations committed to or interested in a hybrid cloud solutions has increased from 81% to 93% since 2017. 89% of organizations still expect to have a meaning on-premises footprint in three years.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Over the past 10 years, storage evolved around two very different directions. Traditional enterprise storage, such as Dell® and HPE®, focused on providing standardized file interfaces (NFS and SMB), on ‘scale-up’ hardware, and snapshots for resiliency. On the other hand, cloud storage, developed by hyperscale companies like Google and Amazon, focused on delivering scale-out solutions on commodity hardware, strong resiliency to hardware failures, but relying on proprietary protocols and APIs for data access.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Cloud solutions is increasing rapidly for its agility, scalability and lower costs. The price for archiving could be as low as 0.1 cents per GB per month. Therefore, the vendors in the market are increasingly offering cloud-based solutions to manage data.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Cloud also provides advanced services, such as machine learning, analytics, and data pipelines, so that customers can use “in place” with their data in cloud.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>What enterprises need today is the best of both solutions. They need to support standardized interfaces like NFS and SMB protocols, to interoperate with existing applications. They need to save critical data “in house” for security and compliance reasons. But they have also need to move to software-defined, web-scale solutions on commodity hardware, just like cloud storage. Web-scale provides multiple advantages like ‘pay-as-you-grow’ consumption, always-on availability, simpler management, and lower costs.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>INDUSTRY TRENDS</strong></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>IDC survey shows the market appears to be in the midst of a transition, with growth coming from integrated appliances and software-defined (virtual) instances in cloud environments[6]. Cloud solutions are one of the most comprehensive tools against cyber-attacks and data breaches. However, if mis- managed, it may pave the way for the attackers to seamlessly enter the database stored on the backup server and use it against the user. Hence, the privacy and security issues act as a major hindrance to the adoption of cloud backup solutions.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>Hybrid Cloud</strong></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Major enterprise storage vendors provide hybrid cloud solutions for users to take advantage of both enterprise storage and cloud. The data can be saved in local storage or cloud or both for different purposes. A virtual appliance can be run in cloud to help data mobility.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Major storage vendors such as Dell® supports copy data to cloud for different uses cases:</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:list -->\r\n<ul><!-- wp:list-item -->\r\n<li> Tiering supports cold data bursting to cloud. Cold data are automatically stored in the cloud. Once they become hot, they will be tiered back to private appliances.</li>\r\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\r\n<li> Cloud archiving enables long-term archival to the cloud, providing a more manageable alternative to tape.</li>\r\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\r\n<li> Cloud replication provides replication with virtual appliances running in the cloud.</li>\r\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\r\n<li> Recovery in the public cloud: Today, leading backup vendors support restoring backup data to servers in the public cloud. The backup data can also be used for test/development purposes in the public cloud. Enterprises utilizes multiple public cloud services from different cloud provider. For example, backup solutions may support cloud integration for tiering, archival, and replication to public cloud services such as Google Cloud Storage Nearline, Microsoft Azure and Amazon S3/Glacier. Secondary storage vendors may need to support multi- cloud solutions for enterprises.</li>\r\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\r\n<!-- /wp:list -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>Comprehensive Appliances</strong></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Second, secondary storage infrastructure is fragmented across different point appliances and clouds, including deduplication appliances, backup servers, archiving appliance, cloud gateways, etc. The complexity also comes from multiple software and management tools. To reduce the complexity and improve efficiency, secondary storage vendors address this issue with comprehensive appliance for all the use cases. Cohesity® is among the vendors that first came up with the concept.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Backup &amp; Archiving Market Report','According to IDC, enterprises data is expected to grow to 93 Zettabytes by 2025. About 80% of that data is secondary data in the form of files, objects, and backups.','publish','open','open','','backup-archiving-market-report','','','2024-08-08 16:15:17','2024-08-08 16:15:17','',0,'https://tech24.wpenginepowered.com/?p=144',0,'post','',0),(146,16,'2024-08-05 21:12:01','2024-08-05 21:12:01','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Market Trends</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>According to ESG reports, 49% of enterprises surveyed now run production applications as their primary public cloud use case, closely followed by business intelligence queries and test/dev. Data protection fell to the number four spot in this survey, with just 40% of respondents saying they were currently using the cloud for backup or archival. This change points to a dramatic increase in the use of the cloud as an application workload destination.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A Flexera survey [4] shows, nearly all organizations have employed multi-cloud. 89% of organizations have a multi-cloud strategy, and most (80%) are taking a hybrid approach, combining the use of both public and private clouds. Private cloud plays an important role in this hybrid approach.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Enterprises often end up with a multi-cloud strategy designed to get the best price performance from each workload. Today, a hybrid, multi-cloud IT environment is the norm, not the exception.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>SMBs (small to midsized businesses) are moving quickly to the public cloud, with 63% of workloads will reside in a public cloud within the next twelve months.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In the past, some organizations hesitated to put certain data in public clouds. The new survey found that many respondents are reconsidering. More than half of them said they will consider moving at least some of the sensitive consumer data or corporate financial data to the cloud.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Organizations continue to increase their cloud spend, although the rate of growth is slowing. The public cloud spend was over budget by an average of 13 percent, down from 24 percent YoY. This could be an indication that some organizations have already deployed high priority applications to the cloud and will continue to expand their cloud footprint but at a less accelerated rate.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Applications are often siloed on different clouds: individual applications are not spanning clouds, as the following figure shows. DR/Failover saw a ten percent gain YoY and is now at 44 percent [4].</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Cloud Data Protection Market Report','According to ESG reports, 49% of enterprises surveyed now run production applications as their primary public cloud use case, closely followed by business intelligence queries and test/dev.','publish','open','open','','cloud-data-protection-market-report','','','2024-08-25 20:59:30','2024-08-25 20:59:30','',0,'https://tech24.wpenginepowered.com/?p=146',0,'post','',0),(147,2,'2024-08-06 05:13:56','2024-08-06 05:13:56','','Register','','publish','closed','closed','','register','','','2024-08-06 05:13:56','2024-08-06 05:13:56','',0,'https://tech24.wpenginepowered.com/register/',0,'page','',0),(148,2,'2024-08-06 05:13:56','2024-08-06 05:13:56','','Activate','','publish','closed','closed','','activate','','','2024-08-06 05:13:56','2024-08-06 05:13:56','',0,'https://tech24.wpenginepowered.com/activate/',0,'page','',0),(150,2,'2024-08-06 06:27:38','2024-08-06 06:27:38','<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Summary</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Ransomware poses a significant threat to organizations of all sizes, but a robust backup strategy can mitigate the risks and ensure rapid recovery. Implementing the 3-2-1 backup strategy, utilizing immutable backups and WORM storage, regularly testing backups, and conducting continuous employee training are essential measures to protect against ransomware attacks. By adopting these recommendations, organizations can enhance their resilience, maintain data integrity, and ensure business continuity in the face of increasingly sophisticated cyber threats.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Key Findings</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Ransomware attacks are increasingly sophisticated, necessitating robust backup strategies for effective detection, protection, and recovery.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>A combination of traditional and modern backup solutions, including cloud and offline backups, significantly enhances resilience against ransomware.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Regular testing and updating of backup protocols are critical to ensure data integrity and quick recovery in the event of an attack.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Employee training and awareness are essential components of a comprehensive ransomware defense strategy.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Recommendations</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Implement a 3-2-1 backup strategy: three copies of your data, on two different media, with one copy stored offsite.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Utilize immutable backups and write-once-read-many (WORM) storage to prevent unauthorized alterations.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Regularly test backups and perform recovery drills to ensure data can be restored quickly and completely.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Conduct continuous employee training programs to raise awareness about ransomware threats and best practices for data protection.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Analysis</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Implement a 3-2-1 Backup Strategy</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The 3-2-1 backup strategy is a foundational approach to data protection that ensures multiple copies of data are stored in diverse locations to mitigate the risk of data loss due to ransomware attacks. This strategy involves keeping three copies of data: the primary data and two backup copies. These copies should be stored on at least two different types of media, such as an internal hard drive and an external storage device. One of these copies should be stored offsite, which could be in a remote physical location or a cloud storage service. By diversifying the storage locations and media, the risk of all copies being compromised simultaneously is significantly reduced.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The key advantage of the 3-2-1 strategy is its simplicity and effectiveness in providing a robust defense against data loss. Even if ransomware encrypts the primary data and the local backup, the offsite backup remains untouched and can be used to restore the affected systems. This strategy also facilitates easier data management and recovery, ensuring that businesses can quickly resume operations with minimal downtime.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Utilize Immutable Backups and WORM Storage</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>mmutable backups and Write-Once-Read-Many (WORM) storage are critical technologies in protecting against ransomware attacks. Immutable backups are designed to prevent data from being changed or deleted once they are created, ensuring that the backup data remains intact and unaltered. WORM storage, on the other hand, allows data to be written once and read multiple times without the possibility of modification. These technologies are particularly effective against ransomware, which typically tries to encrypt or delete backup files to force victims to pay the ransom.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Implementing immutable backups and WORM storage involves selecting the appropriate storage solutions that support these features and integrating them into the existing backup infrastructure. Cloud service providers often offer immutable storage options, making it easier for businesses to adopt these technologies without significant changes to their IT environments. By ensuring that backup data cannot be altered, organizations can confidently restore their systems from backups even after a ransomware attack, reducing the potential impact and recovery time.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Regularly Test Backups and Perform Recovery Drills</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Regularly testing backups and conducting recovery drills are essential practices to ensure that backup systems function correctly and data can be restored swiftly in the event of a ransomware attack. Testing backups involves verifying that backup files are complete, uncorrupted, and accessible. Recovery drills simulate real-world scenarios where data must be restored from backups, helping to identify any issues or bottlenecks in the recovery process.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>These practices are crucial because backup systems can sometimes fail, or backups may become corrupted over time without regular verification. By routinely testing backups and performing recovery drills, organizations can identify and address any problems proactively, ensuring that they are prepared to recover data quickly when needed. Additionally, these exercises help to familiarize IT staff with the recovery process, reducing the likelihood of errors and delays during an actual ransomware attack.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Conduct Continuous Employee Training Programs</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Employee training and awareness are vital components of an effective ransomware defense strategy. Human error is often the weakest link in cybersecurity, with employees inadvertently opening malicious emails or downloading infected files. Continuous training programs aim to educate employees about the latest ransomware threats, how to recognize phishing attempts, and best practices for data protection.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Training programs should include regular updates on emerging threats and interactive exercises, such as simulated phishing attacks, to reinforce learning. By fostering a culture of security awareness, organizations can reduce the likelihood of successful ransomware attacks and enhance their overall cybersecurity posture. Employees who are well-informed and vigilant are better equipped to avoid risky behaviors that could compromise the organization’s data.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Ten backup strategies to detect, protect and recover from ransomware','','publish','closed','closed','','ten-backup-strategies-to-detect-protect-and-recover-from-ransomware','','','2024-08-07 18:54:49','2024-08-07 18:54:49','',0,'https://tech24.wpenginepowered.com/?post_type=market_research&#038;p=150',0,'market_research','',0),(151,2,'2024-08-06 06:26:50','2024-08-06 06:26:50','','Ransomware','','inherit','open','closed','','ransomware','','','2024-08-06 06:26:50','2024-08-06 06:26:50','',150,'https://tech24.wpenginepowered.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Ransomware.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(152,2,'2024-08-06 08:39:16','2024-08-06 08:39:16','','Footer','','publish','closed','closed','','footer','','','2024-08-06 08:39:16','2024-08-06 08:39:16','',0,'https://tech24.wpenginepowered.com/?post_type=elementor-hf&#038;p=152',0,'elementor-hf','',0),(156,2,'2024-08-06 09:47:18','2024-08-06 09:47:18','<style>/*! elementor - v3.23.0 - 05-08-2024 */\n.elementor-widget-image-box .elementor-image-box-content{width:100%}@media (min-width:768px){.elementor-widget-image-box.elementor-position-left .elementor-image-box-wrapper,.elementor-widget-image-box.elementor-position-right .elementor-image-box-wrapper{display:flex}.elementor-widget-image-box.elementor-position-right .elementor-image-box-wrapper{text-align:end;flex-direction:row-reverse}.elementor-widget-image-box.elementor-position-left .elementor-image-box-wrapper{text-align:start;flex-direction:row}.elementor-widget-image-box.elementor-position-top .elementor-image-box-img{margin:auto}.elementor-widget-image-box.elementor-vertical-align-top .elementor-image-box-wrapper{align-items:flex-start}.elementor-widget-image-box.elementor-vertical-align-middle .elementor-image-box-wrapper{align-items:center}.elementor-widget-image-box.elementor-vertical-align-bottom .elementor-image-box-wrapper{align-items:flex-end}}@media (max-width:767px){.elementor-widget-imag