details -->\n\n<!-- wp:details -->\n<details class=\"wp-block-details\"><summary>How do I ask a question or start a discussion?</summary><!-- wp:paragraph {\"placeholder\":\"Type / to add a hidden block\"} -->\n<p>Navigate to a specific community forum home page and click on the \"New Discussion\" on right sidebar. A popup editor window will show and you can enter your discussion title and discussion content there.  Note: </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Images and videos can only be attached at the end of discussion content. </li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Topic tags can be added to tag your discussion.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Your discussion post will go live immediate after posting</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"placeholder\":\"Type / to add a hidden block\"} -->\n<p> <br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"placeholder\":\"Type / to add a hidden block\"} -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></details>\n<!-- /wp:details -->\n\n<!-- wp:details -->\n<details class=\"wp-block-details\"><summary>I made a post or comment but I don’t see it on the platform — why is that?</summary><!-- wp:paragraph {\"placeholder\":\"Type / to add a hidden block\"} -->\n<p>Posts may take some time to show up; additionally, posts and comments may be moderated and/or removed entirely at any time if they are a violation of the platform’s Guidelines. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:details -->\n<details class=\"wp-block-details\"><summary>Where can I find a post that I made previously?</summary><!-- wp:paragraph {\"placeholder\":\"Type / to add a hidden block\"} -->\n<p>You may navigate to your profile page and click the my discussion tab to view your posts in chronological order and able to be filtered by type.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"placeholder\":\"Type / to add a hidden block\"} -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:details -->\n<details class=\"wp-block-details\"><summary>How do I answer a Q&amp;A post?</summary><!-- wp:paragraph {\"placeholder\":\"Type / to add a hidden block\"} -->\n<p>If you want to reply a discussion, you may go to that discussion page and click \"Reply\" below the discussion content. It will open a popup editor to allow you to answer or comment a discussion post. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you want to reply a reply, you may use a reply\'s context menu and click reply to reply that reply. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:details -->\n<details class=\"wp-block-details\"><summary>I’m unable to comment on a post — why is that?</summary><!-- wp:paragraph {\"placeholder\":\"Type / to add a hidden block\"} -->\n<p>Only logged in user can create a discussion or a comment. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:details -->\n<details class=\"wp-block-details\"><summary>How do I share posts?</summary><!-- wp:paragraph {\"placeholder\":\"Type / to add a hidden block\"} -->\n<p>Individual discussions all have a group of social sharing icons at right sidebar.  A pop-up will appear with pre-populated options to share via email, social media, or direct hyperlink.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></details>\n<!-- /wp:details --></details>\n<!-- /wp:details --></details>\n<!-- /wp:details --></details>\n<!-- /wp:details --></details>\n<!-- /wp:details -->','Community FAQ','','publish','closed','closed','','community-faq','','','2024-09-17 18:58:27','2024-09-17 18:58:27','',0,'https://tech24.wpenginepowered.com/?page_id=559',0,'page','',0),(565,2,'2024-10-01 11:06:27','0000-00-00 00:00:00','','Elementor #565','','draft','open','open','','elementor-565','','','2024-10-01 11:06:27','2024-10-01 11:06:27','',0,'https://tech24.wpenginepowered.com/?p=565',0,'post','',0),(575,2,'2024-10-14 12:40:04','0000-00-00 00:00:00','[bandwidth_calculater]','Elementor #575','','draft','open','open','','elementor-575','','','2024-10-14 12:40:05','2024-10-14 12:40:05','',0,'https://tech24.wpenginepowered.com/?p=575',0,'post','',0),(576,14,'2024-10-18 17:42:15','2024-10-18 17:42:15','<p>We currently have an iSCSI LUN configured with two target IPs, supporting ESXi VM storage across multiple hosts using round-robin load balancing. This setup has worked efficiently for over four years.</p><p>However, I’ve recently noticed an increase in storage latency. We\'ve added several VMs, many of which are running SQL databases, and while performance isn’t critical yet, I can see it trending in that direction. I’d like to address the issue before it escalates.</p><p>I\'m considering adding two additional target IPs to the LUN, increasing the total to four. My concern is whether some hosts, which only have access to two of the target IPs, could experience traffic blackholing if the LUN uses all four. Alternatively, will the storage array only respond on the originating IP? I assume it would only respond to the original initiator IP, but I want to confirm.</p><p>For reference, we are using a Dell Unity system. Apologies if this is a basic question—while my background is in networking, I have enough storage knowledge to be cautious.</p>','How to add additional iSCSI target to LUN?','','publish','closed','closed','','how-to-add-additional-iscsi-target-to-lun','','','2024-10-18 17:42:15','2024-10-18 17:42:15','',260,'https://tech24.wpenginepowered.com/forums/discussion/how-to-add-additional-iscsi-target-to-lun/',0,'topic','',0),(577,29,'2024-10-18 18:01:16','2024-10-18 18:01:16','<p>A great question. MPIO functions effectively only across different Layer 2 subnets. You can add as many subnets as needed or consider upgrading your network to higher speeds. Rest assured, there will be no risk of traffic blackholing.</p>','','','publish','closed','closed','','577','','','2024-10-18 18:01:16','2024-10-18 18:01:16','',576,'https://tech24.wpenginepowered.com/forums/reply/577/'